content: It's difficult to say exactly what Madeaux means with "I see you" without additional context or information. However, the repetition of the phrase "some faces I know" and the reference to various locations around the world suggest that the song is about encountering familiar faces or memories in different places. "I see you" could be interpreted as a recognition or acknowledgement of these faces or memories. It's also possible that the phrase has a more metaphorical or abstract meaning related to the theme of the song.
